    diagnostics: ["Comprehensive pain assessment: location, intensity, quality, timing, aggravating/relieving factors", "Assessment of all four pain dimensions: physical, psychological, social, spiritual", "Functional impact assessment: sleep, mobility, ability to interact with loved ones", "Assessment of opioid side effects: constipation, sedation, nausea"],
    management: ["Around-the-clock opioid dosing with breakthrough doses available (typically 10-15% of total daily dose)", "Follow WHO analgesic ladder: escalate based on pain severity", "Adjuvant medications for specific pain types (dexamethasone for bone pain, gabapentin for neuropathic)", "Address psychological, social, and spiritual pain dimensions simultaneously"],
    nursingActions: ["Assess pain regularly using appropriate tools even in non-verbal patients", "Administer prescribed opioids promptly and reassess effectiveness", "Anticipate and prevent opioid side effects (prophylactic bowel regimen is essential)", "Advocate for adequate pain management - there is no maximum opioid dose in palliative care", "Address patient and family fears about opioid use and addiction at end of life"],
